verbose_text: Compared with rapid reversion of para-AZO, Z-ortho-AZO is thermally stable with a long tau 1/2 (the time required for a quantity of Z-AZO to fall to half its value by Z --> E reversion) of 116 hours at room temperature due to the formation of intramolecular H-bonds in Z-isomer (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
